data-triple-N3.o: "Blu-ray Disc (BD) is an optical disc storage medium designed to supersede the DVD format. The plastic disc is 120mm in diameter and 1.2mm thick, the same size as DVDs and CDs. Conventional (pre-BD-XL) Blu-ray Discs contain 25GB per layer, with dual layer discs (50 GB) being the industry standard for feature-length video discs. Triple layer discs (100 GB) and quadruple layers (150 GB) are available for BD-XL re-writer drives."@en
